# [SEAT](../wg/seat.html)

## Summary
The SEAT working group met during IETF 126. Co-chairs **Yaroslav Rosomakho** and **Nancy Cam-Winget** presided over the session. The chairs announced the formal adoption of [draft-ietf-seat-use-cases](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-ietf-seat-use-cases/) as the working group's first official document. 

The meeting featured presentations and technical discussions on use case refinements, a proposed SEAT architecture, the selection criteria for attested TLS protocols, and various transport mechanisms—including early/intra-handshake attestation, remote attestation with exported authenticators (Expat), and application-layer transport using HTTP capsules.

