## Decisions and Action Items

### Decisions
* **[draft-ietf-seat-use-cases](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-ietf-seat-use-cases/)** was adopted as the working group's first official document.
* **Ionut Grigorescu** was appointed as the sole editor of [draft-ietf-seat-use-cases](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-ietf-seat-use-cases/).
* The working group's active documents will be hosted on the [IETF SEAT Working Group GitHub repository](https://github.com/ietf-wg-seat).

### Action Items
* **Ionut Grigorescu** to migrate the use cases draft to the official SEAT GitHub repository and address frozen issues (e.g., threat model definition and boundary alignment with other WGs).
* **Usama Saleem** and **Marcus** to continue their technical exchange on the mailing list regarding Expat binding strength proofs (G1 vs. G3).
* Authors of the Expat transport draft to coordinate with the HTTP Working Group regarding the usage of HTTP capsules and extended connect.

---

## Next Steps
* The working group will continue technical discussions on the mailing list and GitHub to refine the threat models, definitions of freshness, and terminology.
* Once the use cases and architectural discussions mature, the chairs will consider initiating adoption calls for the solution-oriented drafts.